# vd100-ps-ma-client

PS userspace XRT application for the VD100 MA Crossover AIE pipeline.

## Pipeline

```
PS DDR (int32[])
    │
    ▼
mm2s (HLS) ──AXI4-Stream──► AIE mygraph (MA crossover)
                                         │
                              AXI4-Stream▼
                             s2mm (HLS) ──► PS DDR (int32[])
                                                │
                                                ▼
                                   stdout: fast_ma / slow_ma / BUY-SELL-HOLD
```

## AIE kernel constants

| Constant          | Value | Notes                              |
|-------------------|-------|------------------------------------|
| FAST_MA_PERIOD    | 10    | Fast moving average period         |
| SLOW_MA_PERIOD    | 50    | Slow moving average period         |
| BLOCK_SIZE        | 56    | int32 samples per iteration        |
| NUM_MARGIN_SAMPLES| 56    | Must match BLOCK_SIZE (224 B = 32× multiple) |
| Output per block  | 3     | fast_ma, slow_ma, signal           |

## HLS kernel signatures

```cpp
void mm2s(ap_int<32>* mem, hls::stream<ap_axis<32,0,0,0>>& s, int size)
void s2mm(ap_int<32>* mem, hls::stream<ap_axis<32,0,0,0>>& s, int size)
```
Both: `mem = arg[0]` → `group_id(0)` for XRT BO allocation.

## Usage

```bash
# Golden test vector (built-in, matches golden.txt exactly)
vd100-ps-ma-client binary_container_1.xclbin

# Custom price file (one int32 per line, multiple of 56 samples)
vd100-ps-ma-client binary_container_1.xclbin prices.txt
```

## Expected output (golden vector)

```
┌─────────┬──────────┬──────────┬────────┐
│  Block  │ fast_ma  │ slow_ma  │ Signal │
├─────────┼──────────┼──────────┼────────┤
│      1  │    5000  │    5000  │  HOLD  │
│      2  │    4990  │    4990  │  HOLD  │
│      3  │    5051  │    5002  │  BUY   │  ← crossover triggered
│      4  │    5600  │    5600  │  HOLD  │
└─────────┴──────────┴──────────┴────────┘
```

## Build (on yoctoBuilder via Yocto recipe)

```bash
# 1. Copy files to meta-vd100-v3
cp -r vd100-ps-ma-client/  <yocto>/meta-vd100-v3/recipes-apps/

# 2. Add to image recipe (meta-vd100-v3/recipes-core/images/vd100-image.bb)
IMAGE_INSTALL:append = " vd100-ps-ma-client"

# 3. Build
bitbake vd100-ps-ma-client       # test build only
bitbake vd100-image               # full image

# 4. Deploy xclbin to VD100
scp binary_container_1.xclbin root@vd100:/home/root/
```

## Address map (from Vivado Address Editor)

| IP                    | Base Address  | Range |
|-----------------------|---------------|-------|
| MyLEDIP               | 0xA400_0000   | 4K    |
| mm2s_1/s_axi_control  | 0xA401_0000   | 64K   |
| s2mm_1/s_axi_control  | 0xA402_0000   | 64K   |
| DDR (mm2s via NoC)    | 0x0000_0000   | 2G    |
| DDR (s2mm via NoC)    | 0x0000_0000   | 2G    |

## Notes

- **s2mm runs before mm2s** — s2mm must be ready to receive before mm2s fires,
  otherwise the AIE stream stalls.
- `graph.run(N)` where N = number of blocks (iterations).
- `graph.wait()` after DMA completion — ensures AIE has flushed all output.
- xclbin must be the MA-specific one from the co-compiled system project
  (`binary_container_1.xclbin` from `vd100_ma_system_project`).